# Automated Git Integration Guide

## Commit Triggers
- **Feature completion** - When checklist item marked complete
- **Working state** - Code passes test and functions correctly
- **New file creation** - Especially managers/systems
- **Integration success** - Cross-system connections working

## Commit Message Format
```
{type}({scope}): {description}
```

**Types**: feat, fix, refactor, test, docs, style, arch
**Scopes**: grid, input, resources, buildings, enemies, ui, core

**IMPORTANT**: Commit messages must be ONE LINE ONLY. No sub-points, no bullet lists, no detailed descriptions. All detailed information goes in session logs.

## Session Logging Format
```
# Session: {DATE} - Sprint {NUMBER}

## {TIME} - {FEATURE_NAME}
Action: {WHAT_WAS_DONE}
Files: {FILES_MODIFIED}
Test: {TEST_RESULT}
Commit: {COMMIT_HASH} - {COMMIT_MESSAGE}

## Technical Details
- {DETAILED_CHANGES}
- {DECISIONS_MADE}
- {TESTING_NOTES}
- {INTEGRATION_POINTS}
```

## Recovery Commands
- **"Show revert options"** - Display rollback points
- **"Emergency revert"** - Quick rollback to last stable
- **"Commit checkpoint"** - Manual stable state marker